description: A mixed use redevelopment. Demolition of all existing building on the site with the exception of Thorpe Coombe House building. Construction of six blocks (ranging from 2 to 5 storey) to form 91 residential units (21 x 1 bed, 45 x 2 bed, self-contained flats  16 x 3 bed houses and 9 x 4 bed homes) 17 of which to be provided within the conversion of Thorpe Coombe House, new health centre (use class D1) including formation of three access points, parking, open space and landscaping.
